{
  "text": "Binary vectors used for rice transformation, pVM200 (control vector), pVM220 (gh3-gs52) or pMS1-2809 (35Spsl), were introduced into Agrobacterium tumefaciens EHA105 by electroporation [CITATION_1] . A. tumefaciens strains harboring the transformation vectors were grown at 30 8C in Luria-Bertani (LB) broth supplemented with 50 mg ml \u00c01 rifampicin and 100 mg ml \u00c01 kanamycin to an OD 600 of 1.0. The bacterial cells from overnight cultures were harvested by centrifugation at 5000 \u00c2 g for 10 min, washed and resuspended in MSD medium (see below) containing 51 mM acetosyringone (Aldrich, Milwaukee, WI, USA) to a final OD 600 of 0.04-0.06, and used for the transformation of rice calli as described below.",
  "citation_candidates": [
